</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1215,1026,1492]" box="[151,869,1026,1052]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">The group comprises 2 species. It is characterised as follows:</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1215,1026,1492]" box="[199,765,1066,1092]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">­ forewing with some markings absent (apo.);</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1215,1026,1492]" box="[199,709,1106,1132]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">­ ground colour of forewing light brown;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1215,1026,1492]" box="[199,666,1146,1172]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">­ antemedial line well marked, black;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1215,1026,1492]" box="[199,713,1186,1212]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">­ medial shade with black patch on costa;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1215,1026,1492]" box="[199,699,1226,1252]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">­ reniform stigma prominent, yellowish;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1215,1026,1492]" box="[199,674,1266,1292]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">­ hindwing with indistinct discal spot;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1215,1026,1492]" box="[199,526,1306,1332]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">­ saccus short, triangular;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1215,1026,1492]" box="[199,824,1346,1372]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">­ tergite log­like, with stout hair­like setae at apex;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1215,1026,1492]" box="[199,1140,1386,1412]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">­ processes from fultura superior log­like, with medial pointed process (apo.);</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1215,1026,1492]" box="[199,1215,1426,1452]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">­ phallus broadest at ductus ejaculatorius, curved subapically, tapered towards apex;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1215,1026,1492]" box="[199,886,1466,1492]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">­ vesica often with two or three small triangular cornuti;</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
